Mexico Stocks: Desarrolladora Homex, Industrias Penoles, Telmex

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-06-24T20:40:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/mexico-stocks-industrias-penoles-telefonos-de-mexico.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The IPC index rose 0.1 percent to 35,347.85.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX* MM), Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, jumped 3.4 percent to 46.43 pesos as the company’s
valuation relative to other Mexican stocks draws investors,
according to Francisco Suarez Savin, an analyst at HSBC, who
spoke in a phone interview from Mexico City.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, declined 0.2 percent to 435.62 pesos. Silver
futures for September delivery fell for a second day, retreating
as much as 2.4 percent to $34.16 an ounce on the Comex in New
York.  Telefonos de Mexico SAB (TELMEXL MM) fell 0.3 percent to
9.53 pesos, after earlier advancing as much as 0.8 percent.
Mexico’s largest fixed-line telephone company had its foreign
currency issuer default rating raised to A from A- with a stable
outlook by  Fitch Ratings , according to a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
